<P>
   DOG-CHOICES _ As a professional educator, Allen Bower has
learned that the best way to avoid mistakes is to do your homework.
After a series of disasters with dogs that got on his nerves, the
school executive studied up on canines and concluded a Bichon Frise
would be best for his family. The books said its personality was a
good fit. And that's critical, says Dr. Stan Coren, a psychologist
at the University of British Columbia and author of the new hit,
``Why We Love the Dogs We Do.'' (Hendrick, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) WITH PHOTOS AND GRAPHIC. ETA: 8 p.m.
</P>
