<SLUG> BC-WHITE-COLUMN-BOS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
IS IT TIME FOR A BEANIE BABIES BAN?
</HEADLINE>
   &HT;     (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By DIANE WHITE  
 c.1998 The Boston Globe  
<TEXT>
 &QL;
<P>
   A wave of Beanie Baby-related crime is sweeping the nation. Week
after week, reports of new and shocking Beanie Baby criminal
activities come to light. And for every Beanie Baby crime that
makes the news, you can be sure that there are dozens, maybe even
hundreds, more that we never hear about.
</P>
<P>
   How long will this continue? Isn't it time we started talking
about banning the source of the problem?
</P>
<P>
   Last week two residents of Brunswick, Maine, _ one of them a
17-year-old girl _ were arrested and accused by police of
masterminding a heist of between 300 and 400 Beanie Babies,
according to an Associated Press report. They were caught trying to
unload the stolen Beanies in an Auburn store.
</P>
<P>
   The manufacturer, Ty (USA), releases only limited numbers of
each Beanie Baby, which are sold in stores for about $5. The
escalating prices of certain rare collectible Beanies have led to a
flourishing black market that drives the crime wave.
</P>
<P>
   A few Beanies fetch prices of up to $5,000 _ Peanut the Royal
Blue Elephant, Nana the Brown Monkey, Derby the Fine Mane Horse,
among others. Many have a resale value of more than $1,000 _ Bronty
the Brontosaurus, Chilly the Polar Bear, Flutter the Butterfly,
Humphrey the Camel, to name just a few.
</P>
<P>
   Criminals will stop at nothing to get their hands on Beanies.
</P>
<P>
   _ A Nashua, N.H., couple were arrested recently for forging
$2,400 in checks to buy Beanie Babies. According to an AP report,
they told police they bought heroin with the money they made
reselling the Beanies.
</P>
<P>
   _ A registered sex offender in Grand Prairie, Texas, strewed his
parents' front lawn with Beanie Babies in an attempt to lure
children into the house, which is located across from an elementary
school, according to a May 29 report in The Fort Worth
Star-Telegram.
</P>
<P>
   _ In April, robbers hit two Los Angeles store owners on the head
with metal pipes and stole a box of Beanies, along with $1,000 in
cash. ``I can't believe people would damage other people over a
beanbag,'' an unnamed store employee told a reporter from The Los
Angeles Times.
</P>
<P>
   Believe it. These are a few of the most extreme Beanie
Baby-related crimes, but other incidences of thievery, duplicity,
and fraud abound.
</P>
<P>
   A store owner in Westminster, Calif., told The Los Angeles Times
she limits the number of Beanies each customer can buy to one or
two. But some people, she said, come back in disguise to buy more,
or bribe children to buy for them.
</P>
<P>
   Counterfeit Beanie Babies continue to proliferate, according to
Beanie World News, a glossy magazine that bills itself as
``America's Best Selling Beanie Baby Magazine,'' presumably to
distinguish it from all the others.
</P>
<P>
   In March, 52 cartons containing 8,596 fake Beanies from China _
with an approximate street value of $450,000 _ were seized by US
Customs at Chicago's O'Hare Airport. According to Beanie World, the
faux Beanies included ``Flash, Smoochy, Bruno, Snowball, Waves
Spike, Spooky, and Waddle.''
</P>
<P>
   Beanies, real and counterfeit, are being confiscated at the
Canadian border to try to stem the tide of fakes washing into the
United States. Cars are being searched. (Vacationers take note.)
Look for the prices of Maple the Canadian bear and Special Olympics
Maple the Canadian Bear to skyrocket as they become virtually
unavailable, the magazine advises, looking on the bright side.
</P>
<P>
   Is it time for a Beanie ban? I know what some of you are
thinking: If Beanie Babies are outlawed, only outlaws will have
Beanie Babies. Which might be just fine with some parents who are
getting sick of the things and all the hysteria that attends them.
Meanwhile, Beanie Baby crime marches on.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (Diane White is a columnist with The Boston Globe.)
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
