<HEADLINE>
`FAST, CHEAP' ENERGETIC; `BREAST MEN' THOUGHTFUL 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By MICHAEL BLOWEN  
 c.1998 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW RELEASES:  &UR; ``Fast, Cheap and Out of Control''  &LR; _ Errol
Morris, who brings a novelist's sensibilities to his nonfiction
films, hits on all cylinders with this energetic appreciation of
four intelligent dreamers whose aspirations are just a bit off
center. Unlike many filmmakers, Morris doesn't force his subjects
into pre-created situations. He allows them to be their complicated
selves.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ``Breast Men''  &LR; _ Another example of HBO's continuing
production of thoughtful, offbeat movies. Two doctors rise to fame
by performing breast-enhancement surgery. David Schwimmer of
``Friends'' is terrific as one of the doctors, and the film raises
issues in both a comic and serious vein.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ``Mr. Magoo''  &LR; _ Jim Backus's voice for the cartoon was perfect
and funny. The same jokes don't work in live action, even though
Leslie Nielsen, a good sport, does his best. It's not good enough.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ``Past Perfect''  &LR; _ Action and car chases and Eric Roberts all
add up to a science-fiction B movie. Viewers who go for this stuff
won't mind that the writing is bad and the plot stupid. There's
enough action to satisfy even fans of ``The Jerry Springer Show.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ``The Postman''  &LR; _ This pretentious claptrap proves one thing:
Kevin Costner is a star. If he weren't, he'd be &UR;  &LR; licking stamps in
a rehab program for bad filmmakers &UR;  &LR; after this one.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
---- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   COMING ATTRACTIONS:  &UR; June 30: &LR;  ``Amistad,'' ``Half Baked,''
``Retroactive,'' ``The Replacement Killers,'' ``This World, Then
the Fireworks,'' ``When Danger Follows You Home,'' ``No Looking
Back,'' ``When Pigs Fly,'' ``Police Story,'' ``Ma Vie en Rose (My
Life in Pink).''  &UR; July 1:  &LR; ``Wag the Dog.''  &UR; July 7:  &LR; ``Good Will
Hunting,'' ``The Boxer,'' ``Six O'Clock News,'' ``Baby Monitor:
Sound of Fear.''  &UR; July 14:  &LR; ``Phantoms,'' ``The Winter Guest,''
``Plato's Run,'' ``Nil by Mouth,'' ``The Night Caller,'' ``The Call
of the Wild: Dog of the Yukon,'' ``French Exit,'' ``Swept From the
Sea,'' ``Illtown,'' ``Chairman of the Board.''  &UR; July 21:  &LR; ``Great
Expectations,'' ``Four Days in September,'' ``Krippendorf's
Tribe,'' ``Two Friends,'' ``The Education of Little Tree,''
``Kissing a Fool,'' ``Prince Valiant,'' ``Children of the Corn V:
Fields of Terror.''  &UR; July 28:  &LR; ``The Gingerbread Man,'' ``The
Peacekeper,'' ``Paperback Romance,'' ``Dark City,'' ``A Kid in
Aladdin's Palace,'' ``Live Flesh.''  &UR; July 31:  &LR; ``Cousin
