   COURT-HARASSMENT (Washington) _ 1stld-writethru to be filed _
School districts cannot be held responsible when a teacher sexually
harasses a student if the school authorities were not informed of
the misconduct, the Supreme Court rules in a case from Lago Vista,
Texas. By MARK HELM.
</P>
<P>
   EXCESSIVE-FINE (Washington) _ For the first time, the Supreme
Court declares a fine excessive and unconstitutional, allowing a
Los Angeles man to recover $340,000 that was seized by the
government. By MARK HELM.
