   MAURO-BUSH (Washington) _ Garry Mauro, the Democratic
gubernatorial candidate in Texas, tells the National Press Club why
incumbent Gov. George W. Bush would make a bad president. The
speech comes on the heels of Bush's million-dollar fund-raising
spree in the nation's capital, where he was welcomed as a potential
Republican presidential candidate in 2000. By BENNETT ROTH.
</P>
