   &UR; QUOTABLES FROM NBC'S 'THE TONIGHT SHOW WITH JAY LENO' &LR;
</P>
<P>
   Louise Woodward, the British nanny, now back home in England.
Gee, I wonder if any of those people who were cheering for her in
that pub will help her out now, maybe give her a babysitting job.
</P>
<P>
   Talk about brave new world. I don't know whether this is creepy
or science or what, but for the first time ever, a woman has given
birth on the Internet. She's fine, the baby's fine, the keyboard's
a mess.
</P>
<P>
   And, God bless him, 78-year-old Tony Randall became a father
again. His wife gave birth to their second child. Tony says he just
wants to live long enough to see his kids graduate preschool.
</P>
<P>
   Paula Jones is getting a nose job. Which I think is great. Now,
she'll finally be able to turn around in her trailer.
</P>
<P>
   It seems Whitney Houston and Bobby Brown announced they are
separating. Apparently, it's over career differences. I guess she
has one.
