<HEADLINE>
FLORIDA'S TURNBERRY ISLE RESORT OFFERS PAMPERING 

</HEADLINE>
  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  By HARRY SHATTUCK 
1998c. Houston Chronicle 
<TEXT>
<P>
   AVENTURA, Fla. _ Whether your main vacation objective is
golfing, tennis or merely an urge to be pampered, Turnberry Isle
Resort &AMP; Club represents an ideal respite between Miami and Fort
Lauderdale, Fla.
</P>
<P>
   Rates are at their lowest in summer, too, at this 300-acre
Mediterranean-style resort touted by Zagat's U.S. Hotel, Resort and
Spa Survey as the best Miami-area hotel (tied with Grand Bay in
Coconut Grove) and for offering the best rooms and service.
</P>
<P>
   Among enticements: two 18-hole golf courses designed by Robert
Trent Jones, 24 tennis courts, a 117-slip marina for deep sea
fishing and charter yachts, the private Ocean Club on the Atlantic
and a full-service spa.
</P>
<P>
   At the resort's much-honored Veranda Restaurant, chef Todd
Weisz's ``New World'' cuisine combines South Florida's tropical
flavors with a blend of Cuban, Caribbean and Latin American
influences.
</P>
<P>
   Most accommodations are in the ``Country Club,'' accented by
gardens and a courtyard pool. Rooms include two televisions and a
marble bath with separate whirlpool tub and shower.
</P>
<P>
   Golf and tennis are a major focus. Several surveys rank
Turnberry Isle among the nation's top 50 golf resorts. Many tennis
pros train here, and instruction is provided for all levels.
</P>
<P>
   Special promotions available through Sept. 30 include a
two-night minimum golf package, with unlimited daily green fees,
for $139 per person per night, based on double occupancy. (It's
$319 per person in midwinter.) Sampler packages start at $89.50 per
person per night, double occupancy, and include accommodations,
breakfast, one round of golf, one hour of tennis and a one-day spa
admission.
</P>
<P>
   Contact a travel agent or call 800-327-7028 for more information
or reservations. Access http://www.turnberryisle.com on the
Internet.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
