(For use by NYTimes News Service clients) The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following stories
today for use by NYTimes News Service clients. They will move in
the ``e'' entertainment news file. For questions, contact Jimmy
Johnson at the Daily News, (818) 713-3695. 
. 
SHEEDY-MOVIE (Los Angeles) _ Once the Brat Pack cachet wore off,
Ally Sheedy says, she began casting about for serious, ``darker''
roles. That's not so easy for an actress with a suburban
girl-next-door image. But she's finally landed a grownup part,
playing Lucy Berliner, a tortured, drug-abusing, agonizingly thin
photographer in ``High Art.'' By Bob Strauss. 
. 
BRIDE-MUSIC (Los Angeles) _ June is traditionally the month to be
merry _ and get married. In the spirit of union comes a new CD
compilation that collects the most popular wedding songs of all
time. By Fred Shuster.
