<SLUG> BC-BRIDE-MUSIC-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
WHAT, NO `TITANIC' LOVE SONG?
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By FRED SHUSTER 
c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ June is traditionally the month to be merry _ and
get married.
</P>
<P>
   In the spirit of union comes a new CD compilation that collects
the most popular wedding songs of all time.
</P>
<P>
   You already know some of these tunes _ ``Promises Ain't Enough''
by Hall &AMP; Oates, ``A Whole New World (Aladdin's Theme)'' by Peabo
Bryson with Regina Belle, ``Endless Love'' by Diana Ross &AMP; Lionel
Richie, ``I Pledge My Love'' by Peaches &AMP; Herb, and ``Best Thing
That Ever Happened to Me'' by Gladys Knight &AMP; the Pips.
</P>
<P>
   Bookending the 15-track disc, titled ``Modern Bride Presents the
Wedding Album'' (Columbia), are the two most familiar pieces of
traditional wedding music: the ``Bridal Chorus'' from Richard
Wagner's ``Lohengrin'' and the ``Wedding March'' from Felix
Mendelssohn's ``A Midsummer Night's Dream,'' Op. 61.
</P>
<P>
   The making of the album was a group effort, said Dave
Santaniello, vice president of special marketing at Columbia
Records in New York.
</P>
<P>
   The initial list of songs was compiled by Santaniello's
assistant, Lauri Pearson, who came up with the titles from memory
after having spent several years in radio.
</P>
<P>
   ``She knew the songs from the number of on-air requests they
received,'' Santaniello said.
</P>
<P>
   ``The Wedding Album'' is being marketed with Modern Bride
magazine, the nation's top wedding mag. In fact, 350,000 copies of
the August/September issue will contain a sampler featuring spoken
word from Pearson and samples of romantic songs from some of
Columbia's new artists, including Chantal Kreviazuk and Bic Runga.
</P>
<P>
   ``Choosing the music you'll hear at your wedding and your
reception is surely one of the most personal wedding-planning
decisions of all,'' said Stacy Morrison, editor of Modern Bride.
</P>
<P>
   But where's Celine Dion's ``My Heart Will Go On,'' the
international smash that just may be this summer's most popular
wedding song?
</P>
<P>
   Santaniello said ``The Wedding Album'' was being created six
months ago, just as the blockbuster ``Titanic'' was taking off, so
it was too soon to include Dion's song.
</P>
<P>
   ``We'd like to do this on a yearly basis,'' Santaniello said,
adding that next year's package would probably include the
``Titanic'' love theme.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
