<P>
   By Art Thiel. (story will move in the ``s'' category)
</P>
<P>
   GLF-SAHALEE (San Francisco) They are West Coast courses ripe
with trees on every hole, tight fairways, several steep inclines,
right and left doglegs, and well-fertilized rough that can swallow
balls skipping only inches off course. One is laden with history
while the other has history waiting to be made. The Olympic Club
Lake Course and Redmond's Sahalee Country Club, site of this year's
PGA Championship Aug. 10-16, have so much in common that deja vu
might strike many of the players who completed in the U.S. Open
here.
</P>
<P>
   By Angelo Bruscas. (story will move in the ``s'' category)
