 &HT;    On deck for Atlanta: New York Yankees
 &HT;    By Jack Wilkinson
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   _ When: 7:35 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   _ Where: Yankee Stadium.
</P>
<P>
   _ TV/radio: TBS.
</P>
<P>
   _ Probable starting pitchers: LHP Tom Glavine (9-3, 2.75 ERA;
0-0, 0.00 lifetime vs. Yankees) vs. RHP Orlando Hernandez (2-0,
1.52; first appearance vs. Braves).
</P>
<P>
   _ Notes: Glavine, who had his five-game winning streak snapped
by Florida last Thursday, returns to the scene of one of his best
performances last season. In the opener of a three-game interleague
series, Glavine threw nine innings of eight-hit (all singles),
shutout ball before the Yankees hit four straight singles off Mike
Bielecki in the 10th inning to win 1-0. That was one of Glavine's
12 no-decisions last season. Tonight, he goes after his 10th win.
Two Yankees have had success against Glavine in the past: Darryl
Strawberry, with three home runs in 32 at-bats (8-for-32, .250);
and Tim Raines (4-for-13, .308). Hernandez makes his fourth
major-league start since being called up from Class AAA Columbus.
After winning his first two starts, El Duque got no decision in a
5-2 win last Thursday in Cleveland. He gave up seven hits and two
earned runs in 7-2/3 innings, and was hoping to become only the
fourth Yankee to start and win his first big-league appearances
(and the first since Mel Stottlemyre in 1964). Opponents are
hitting just .198 against Hernandez (16-for-81, one homer). He's
been especially tough against right-handed hitters (.143, 5-for-35;
lefties are .11-for-46, .239, one homer).
</P>
