<HEADLINE>
AFTER NAFTA, EL PASO AND OTHER BORDER CITIES FACE HIGH
UNEMPLOYMENT 
</HEADLINE>
  
 (SUBS for art note; no other changes)   (ART ADV.: a graphic and a photo are being sent to NYT photo and
graphics clients. Non-subscribers may make individual purchase by
calling 212 556-4204.) 
 (ps) 
 By SAM HOWE VERHOVEK   
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   EL PASO, Texas _ Four years after the North American Free Trade
Agreement lowered trade barriers, the cities along Texas' long
border with Mexico that had hoped to benefit are instead struggling
to become more than glorified truck stops as they watch their
manufacturing jobs go south by the thousands.
</P>
<P>
   End new lead. Pick up 2nd graf, beginning: Almost everywhere
else x x x, and continue as sent.
</P>
