<SLUG> BC-COMPANIES-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
COMPANY NEWS 
(HLW) 
</HEADLINE>
  c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   MBIA Inc., Armonk, N.Y., a guarantor of municipal bonds, agreed
to buy 1838 Investment Advisors, of Radnor, Pa., an investment
management firm with $6 billion in assets, for undisclosed terms.
</P>
<P>
   Metro Holdings AG, Cologne, Germany, plans to buy a 12.5 percent
stake in the phone company RSL Communications Ltd., Hamilton,
Bermuda, for $30 million as part of an agreement to sell RSL phone
services in Europe.
</P>
<P>
   Thomson Corp., Toronto, said its unit Thomson Financial Services
Europe had acquired Tudor House Publications Ltd., a privately
owned British publisher. Terms were not disclosed.
</P>
</TEXT>
