near Bouafle, where he has been forced to work as a slave on a corn
plantation since he was tricked into going there by promises of
work, housing and pay. His story is emblematic of thousands of
coerced migrant laborers, many of them children, in this
overwhelmingly agricultural country. (Robert Grossman/New York
