   &UR; BUSINESS DAY _ (Moved in ``f'' category)  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   CISCO-MARKETPLACE (Undated) _ Cisco Systems Inc., acknowledging
that it has tried and failed to forge partnerships with Lucent
Technologies Inc. and Northern Telecom of Canada, now intends to
continue alone in defending its leadership in the increasingly
competitive market for advanced data networking equipment. By Seth
Schiesel.
</P>
<P>
   CANADA-ECON (Regina, Saskatchewan) _ It has become a regular,
lmost routine, occurrence: another day, another record low for the
Canadian dollar. Its currency is worth around 68 U.S. cents, just
above the record low. Yet, despite the best attempts of chauvinist
columnists and all-news radio stations to stir things up every time
the Canadian dollar weakens, Canadians are acting as though nothing
much has happened. By Anthony DePalma.
</P>
