<P>
   BANKERS-TRUST _ Having survived a series of financial scandals
that tarnished the vaunted trading house's reputation and tore into
its bottom line in recent years, Bankers Trust is refashioning
itself as investment banker to the nation's _ indeed, the world's _
smaller, fast-growth companies. By Timothy L. O'Brien.
</P>
<P>
   TEXAS-AD-COLUMN (Dallas) _ Despite the sometimes arduous task of
appearing Texan enough to suit outsiders, the Lone Star State's
commercial production companies report a growing business. The
state now ranks third _ or perhaps fourth _ in the amount of money
spent there to make TV commercials, according to Jeff Klein,
executive director of the Texas Association of Film/Tape
Professionals. By Carol Marie Cropper.
